7 SECTION 4. Arkansas Code ยง 7-6-209(d), concerning reports of
8 contributions not required for candidates for county office and resulting
9 from Initiated Act 1 of 1996, is amended to read as follows:
10 (d) Reports Not Required.
11 (1) A candidate who has not received contributions or made
12 expenditures in excess of five hundred dollars ($500) shall not be required
13 to file any preelection reports required under subdivision (a)(1) subsection
14 (a) of this section.
15 (2) A candidate who has received contributions or made
16 expenditures in excess of five hundred dollars ($500) but not exceeding five
17 thousand dollars ($5,000) shall only file:
18 (A) A preelection report required under subdivision
19 (a)(1)(B) of this section; and
20 (B) A final report required under subdivision (a)(1)(C) of
21 this section.
22 (3) In calculating the amount of contributions received or
23 expenditures made for purposes of this exception, the payment of the filing
24 fee from the candidate's personal funds shall not be considered as either a
25 contribution or an expenditure.
